Description: Floor sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery bowl (?); slight ridge around central disc on underside; glazed black on interior and exterior save for the disc, which has dot and circle in glaze at the centre; impressed decoration on interior (circle of enclosed ovules, unlinked palmettes); inscription cut on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1816)
